In a #small pot{}, bring 1 ½ cups @water{1 1/2%cups} to boil with a large pinch of @salt{}. Halve, peel, and dice the @yellow onion{1}(halved, peeled, and diced). Peel and mince @ginger{1%thumb}(peeled and minced). Mince the @serrano pepper{1}(minced), removing the ribs and seeds if you prefer less heat. Drain and rinse the @chickpeas{13.4%oz}. Finely chop the @cilantro{1/4%oz}(finely chopped). Trim, then cut the @green beans{6%oz}(trimmed and cut into 2-inch pieces).

Cook the rice: Add the @basmati rice{3/4%cup} to the boiling water, cover, and reduce to a low simmer for ~{15-20%minutes}, until tender.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add the onion to the pan and cook, tossing for ~{4-5%minutes}, until softened. Add the @curry powder{1%tsp}, ginger, and as much Serrano pepper as you like to the pan. Cook, tossing for ~{2-3%minutes}, until very fragrant. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the chickpeas, @diced tomatoes{14%oz}, ½ cup @water{1/2%cup}, and the green beans to the pan and simmer for ~{15%minutes}, until thickened. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Stir ¼ cup @yogurt{5.3%oz} and half the cilantro into the pan. Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Finish and Plate: Serve on a bed of basmati rice, garnish with the remaining cilantro and yogurt. Enjoy!